Exercise 3.37: What does the following program do?

const char ca[] = {'h', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o'};
const char *cp = ca;
while (*cp) {
cout << *cp << endl;
++cp;
}

Answer:
The following program will start by printing hello letter by letter but because there is no null terminator at the end the program will continue to print the following 
areas in the memory until it will encounter a null terminator.
